# 🛠️ Setup Guide

Follow the steps below to set up your development environment for the TinyML course.

---

## 📥 Required Software

Please download and install the following tools:

### 1. Arduino IDE
Used for programming microcontrollers.

👉 Download here:  
https://www.arduino.cc/en/software/

---

### 2. Python
Required for running scripts, data processing, and model handling.

👉 Download here:  
https://www.python.org/downloads/

---

### 3. OpenMV IDE
Used for working with OpenMV cameras and embedded vision applications.

👉 Download here:  
https://openmv.io/pages/download

---

### 4. Docker Desktop
Used to create consistent development environments and manage containers.

👉 Download here:  
https://www.docker.com/

---

### 5. MQTT Explorer
A tool to visualize and debug MQTT communication between devices.

👉 Download here:  
https://mqtt-explorer.com/

---

## ✅ Installation Tips

- Make sure all software is successfully installed before starting the course.
- Restart your computer after installing Docker Desktop.
- Verify Python installation by running:
```bash
python --version
